Privacy Policy for The Spotter

Effective Date: 11/30/2023

Thank you for using The Spotter! This Privacy Policy describes how we collect, use, and disclose personal information when you use our mobile application The Spotter ("App").

Information Collection and Use

Personal Information: We may collect fitness-related data (e.g., steps, distance, calories burned) to provide the game's features. No personal information is collected by this app.

Usage Data: No information on how you use the app will be collected. All data used by the app is stored locally.

Information Sharing and Disclosure

Service Providers: We do not employ any third-party services.

Children's Privacy

Our App does not address anyone under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If we discover that a child under 13 has provided us with personal information, we will promptly delete it.

Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. You are advised to review this page periodically for any changes. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page.

Contact Us

If you have any questions or suggestions about our Privacy Policy, do not hesitate to contact us at spencer_russell@att.net.
